22/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Four members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) and a Turkish soldier were killed during clashes in southeast Turkey on Saturday (August 21st). Authorities say it happened in Hakkari province when security forces came across a group of PKK members. On August 13th, the PKK announced a unilateral ceasefire until September 20th, in observance of Ramadan. They vowed rebels would halt operations inside Turkey, but would defend themselves if attacked by the army. (Anadolu news agency, Xinhua, AFP, CNN-Turk - 21/08/10)
